title: 'Disappointing Quality - Jeans Fades and Ruins Other Clothes'
body: 'I recently purchased a pair of jeans from Amazon and I am deeply dissatisfied with the quality of the product. After just a few washes the jeans started bleeding colors excessively. Every time I wash them my laundry bucket (balti) turns into a mess of faded colors ruining not only the jeans themselves but also other clothes in the same wash.  This level of color bleeding is highly unacceptable and has caused significant inconvenience. I expected a basic level of quality from a product sold on Amazon but this purchase has left me thoroughly disappointed.  I strongly advise against buying this particular pair of jeans. The poor quality and lack of colorfastness have made this purchase a complete waste of money. I hope this review serves as a warning to potential buyers and I will be seeking a refund for this subpar product.'
